\nater ignorance. Any act done under ignorance will yield only further bondag=\r\ne and eclipse, and trap the soul into the chakravyuha(tornado) of the maaya=\r\n.&gt;&gt;\n\n \nYou claim that there is no &quot;eclipse&quot; or covering or bondage in the f=\r\nirst place (because it is &quot;ignorance&quot; and not real) and yet speak of &quot;furth=\r\ner bondage and eclipse&quot;! How can something that doesn&#39;t even exist, increas=\r\ne or decrease?\n\n \n\n2.     The truth is that the divinity is not eclipsed-ne=\r\nither it was, nor it is, and nor it will ever be . There is an illusion in =\r\nour mind that the divinity is eclipsed. This illusion becomes =E2=80=9Creal=\r\n=E2=80=9D and behaves as if it is real. Once the illusion becomes real, it =\r\nstarts affecting us or perhaps seem to affect us in =E2=80=9Creal=E2=80=9D,=\r\n and trying to get rid of it, will only put us in a deeper grip of the appa=\r\nrent reality. The illusion of truth though not real, yet appears as real, i=\r\ns what is defined as =E2=80=9Cmaayaa=E2=80=9D. So your point that something=\r\n that doesn=E2=80=99t even exist yet it seems to increase or decrease, as i=\r\nf it is existing, is a very valid point, and that=E2=80=99s what is defined=\r\n as =E2=80=9Cmaayaa=E2=80=9D. The technical definition of maaya is somethin=\r\ng which though not existing yet appears to exist. I think this explains you=\r\nr point.\n \nIt EITHER does not exist at all OR exists and keeps increasing/d=\r\necreasing. You can&#39;t have it both ways! :-)\n\n3.     =E2=80=9CIt does not ex=\r\nist at all=E2=80=9D is  true. =E2=80=9CIt exists and keeps increasing/decre=\r\nasing=E2=80=9D is also true. And this is what Maaya is-- To give you a feel=\r\ning of existence even though, in truth, it is not existing.\n\n\n \nNow let us =\r\nexamine these 2 cases separately.\n \nCase 1: Eclipse/bondage does not even e=\r\nxist. So it does not increase/decrease. There is nothing to discuss! :-)\n \n=\r\nCase 2: Eclipse/bondage exists and some acts increase it and some decrease =\r\nit. It is not merely efforts to &quot;overcome&quot; this eclipse/bondage that may in=\r\ncrease it. So many other acts could increase it. Some people may have engag=\r\ned in too many such activities and accumulated so much eclipse/bondage/cove=\r\nring of the innate divinity that it may actually need a lot of effort to un=\r\ndo it!\n \n\n4.     Both the cases are true, and that is what maaya is. But on=\r\ne is absolute truth, and another is a perceived truth or relative truth, so=\r\n an illusion of truth.\n\n\n*        *        *\n \nIt is very easy to claim tha=\r\nt all is god and that even considering that there is some covering is an ig=\r\nnorance.\n\n5.     The statement =E2=80=9Call is god=E2=80=9D has a logical e=\r\nrror. When you make such a statement you implicitly define and differentiat=\r\ne two different entities viz.1. All and 2. God. So, if your statement is su=\r\nppose to imply non-duality, it suffers an inherent or implicit contradictio=\r\nn in its very assumption itself where it assumes two separate, distinct, du=\r\nal entities. When you are truly disposed off in non-duality, you cannot mak=\r\ne any such statements.\n\n\n \nThough everything is Self, Self is that which is=\r\n unborn and un-perishing. We are surrounded by many manifestations of Self =\r\nthat are transient, i.e. they are born and they perish. When we come in con=\r\ntact with them, we do not focus on their imperishable essence, but focus on=\r\n the transient/perishable portion that is more readily perceptible to our s=\r\nenses, manas, buddhi and chitta.\n \nThis perishable/transient portion is wha=\r\nt we mean by covering/eclipse.\n\n6.     No Dear Vipravara(learned person). T=\r\nhis perishable transient portion is not eclipse/covering/bondage. How can y=\r\nou have a perishable entity, when the only entity that exist is itself impe=\r\nrishable. Let me take an example. Lets have a gold metal. Lets make three e=\r\nntities with that gold-viz.1. bangles 2. Necklace 3. Ear-rings. Each have d=\r\nifferent entities and functions and properties and behavior and of course n=\r\name. Now let us focus on bangle. Bangle is something which is  circular, an=\r\nd appears different from necklace and ear-rings. Now, I take a 20 gm gold, =\r\nand give it a shape and name and call it bangle. Now, does the bangle exist=\r\n in true sense? No. Now, I melt the bangle, it turns back to 20 gm gold wit=\r\nh no shape and name. So what was existing throughout is the =E2=80=9Cgold=\r\n=E2=80=9D itself, and nothing else. Now you call this bangle as a perishabl=\r\ne entity. But the point is -it is not any entity at all, in the first place=\r\n. It is only a verbal and fictitious entity existing only in words and mind=\r\n, not in actuality. Gold is the only entity existing in actuality. Bangle i=\r\ns just a name given to a form and shape of  gold.\n\n \n\nNow let me come back =\r\nto what eclipse/covering/bondage is. The point is there is no such thing. I=\r\nt is only an illusion or imagination that we are bonded/eclipsed/covered. T=\r\nhe very fact to consider gold to be eclipsed as bangle, and bangle to be pe=\r\nrishable, transient entity, etc=E2=80=94all this is avidya.\n\n \n\nLet me give=\r\n you an incidence of a beautiful Himalayan Sage called Swami Rama with his =\r\n Master. Once Swami Rama asked his master to teach him what avidya or maaya=\r\n or illusion is? His master explained that avidya is individual illusion/ig=\r\nnorance and maaya is cosmic illusion or ignorance. Swami Raama further aske=\r\nd the nature of avidya. His master told that he will explain it later. Then=\r\n suddenly his master jumped on a tree and held it tightly clinging onto its=\r\n trunk and hugging it with his legs crossed across the trunk of the tree. H=\r\ne shouted=E2=80=9DRaamaa, Raamaa, please help me, save me.I am trapped by t=\r\nhis tree. =E2=80=9C Swami Raamaa laughed and said =E2=80=9CHow silly? How c=\r\nan this tree trap you? It has no power to trap you. It is you who have caug=\r\nht hold of it. Just make a decision to quit that hold. Then you will be fre=\r\ne=E2=80=9D His master smiled. And said this is what I mean by illusion or a=\r\nvidya. Though it has got no power to eclipse the Self, yet it appears to ha=\r\nve eclipsed the self. This illusion occurs when the intellect is rendered b=\r\nlind, and not in the state of =E2=80=9Cpragnya=E2=80=9D.\n\n\n \nSuppose one&#39;s =\r\nleg is cut off, blood starts to gush out and one is about to die in a littl=\r\ne time. Can one remain equanimous during that time and genuinely think &quot;thi=\r\ns body and the blood I perceive are transient. They are actually manifestat=\r\nions of imperishable Self. I do not care about transient manifestations. I =\r\nonly care about the imperishable Self. I am Self&quot;?\n\n \n\n7.     Under such ci=\r\nrcumstances, if you are truly in non-dual state of your self, you will simp=\r\nly do the needful, that is try to approach a suitable vaidya and treat your=\r\n case with a suitable medicine(this is karma yoga too). If you start thinki=\r\nng that =E2=80=9Cyou are self=E2=80=9D, then this is wrong. Why? Let me exp=\r\nlain. The very fact that you are =E2=80=9Creacting to=E2=80=9D the leg-cut =\r\noff incidence, itself by default implicitly assumes that you are giving imp=\r\nortance/attachment to that incidence and not treating it as =E2=80=9CSelf=\r\n=E2=80=9D. As a consequence of that reaction, you develop an excited state =\r\nof mind, which you are trying to pacify by means of auto-suggestions like =\r\n=E2=80=9CI am Self. I don=E2=80=99t care about perishable.etc etc=E2=80=9D.=\r\n This auto-suggestion proves the fact that you are already a victim of an i=\r\nncidence, and hence implicitly you are contradicting the non-duality. So in=\r\n essence, it is a hypocrisy.\n \nThis is just one example. Depending on the p=\r\nerson, many such examples can be given, where pretensions of &quot;I am Self&quot; ca=\r\nn be shattered and one will beg &quot;forget about Self. I am in deep trouble. S=\r\nomebody please help me out of this situation&quot;!\n \nIf one is established in S=\r\nelf and NO situation ever disturbs one&#39;s equanimity, only then one is reali=\r\nzed. Such a state is not easy to achieve as some pseudo-Vedantins may sugge=\r\nst.\n\n \n\n8.     Perhaps what I can understand from you is that you had read =\r\nthe views of many scholars or vedantins which have truly bugged your mind, =\r\nand your vocabulary and language patterns too. There appears too much of ju=\r\nngles of words rather than clarity of concepts. This trap of pseudo-wisdom =\r\nis a result of too much playing with words with a very suave and subtle imp=\r\nlicit faulty assumptions not apparently traceable by gullible minds. This h=\r\nappens when too many vedaantin scholars try to write too many bhaashyaas to=\r\n show their scholarly might.\n \nAs I said below, this is just a case of &quot;a l=\r\nong path of constant contemplation and self-correction can be reduced to a =\r\nquick delusional jump to the end&quot;. Unless one catches it whenever something=\r\n transient and perishable is drawing one&#39;s attention, one will not overcome=\r\n each such instinct. Until each such instinct is overcome, &quot;all is imperish=\r\nable Self&quot; is just a theory one is repeating like a parrot. The covering/ec=\r\nlipse/bondage is quite real until then.\n\n \n\n9.     The unreal seems real an=\r\nd as you said, we have to bear with the =E2=80=9Cunreal=E2=80=9D as =E2=80=\r\n=9Creal=E2=80=9D till realization dawns. But the point is it can never dawn=\r\n if you stay out there just doing this. In other words, no efforts can reac=\r\nh us to the state of truth. The truth has to reveal itself. Truth reveals i=\r\ntself for an open and receiving heart. And all this so-called unreal illusi=\r\nons; and the turmoils they are going to create, ultimately lead to the clea=\r\nnsing of heart, finally leading to the truth. Very simple yet very complica=\r\nted indeed. That=E2=80=99s what maaya is..:)\n\n \n\n*        *        *\n \nUnfo=\r\nrtunately, some assertions of Jnana Yoga and Adwaita Vedanta can be mislead=\r\ning. I will try to explain it with a nice analogy from physics.\n \nThis worl=\r\nd is made up of different objects. They are made up of molecules with a lot=\r\n of vacuum in between them. Molecules are made up of atoms and a lot of vac=\r\nuum in between them. Atoms are made up of electrons, protons etc and a lot =\r\nof vacuum in between them. Even those particles are made up of smaller part=\r\nicles and a lot of vacuum in between them. As you keep dividing, you will s=\r\nee that things are made up of subtle portions of matter and a lot of vacuum=\r\n. When you go to the level of small particles, work by physicists such as H=\r\neisenberg, Broglie, Schroedinger etc says that you can&#39;t even observe and d=\r\netermine the properties of those particles confidently without affecting th=\r\nem. They may not even exist as &quot;matter&quot; with specific location and momentum=\r\n or even as waves, independent of the observer.\n \nHowever, despite that &quot;qu=\r\nantum mechanics&quot; reality at the subtlest level, we have normal &quot;mechanics&quot; =\r\ntoo. A lot of gross objects made up of  those subtle particles are gross en=\r\nough and obey some grosser laws of physics (e.g. Newton&#39;s laws). We can fin=\r\nd their positions, momentum etc accurately and make them move deterministic=\r\nally.\n \nWhen one is designing a car or a pulley system or a rocket, one can=\r\n leave quantum mechanics and use normal mechanics. However, when one is doi=\r\nng research on bosons etc, one must pay attention to quantum mechanics. Oth=\r\nerwise, one will commit errors.\n \nSimilarly, at the subtlest level, Self al=\r\none exists. Things that seem to exist may not even exist independent of the=\r\n observer. However, there are also the laws of karma that govern the grosse=\r\nr reality (body, health, job, spouse, children, house, car, money etc). Ris=\r\nhis taught Adwaita Vedanta and also the laws that govern the world of duali=\r\nty (e.g. the law of karma).\n \nWhen one&#39;s awareness focuses on gross objects=\r\n and one is working with the gross world, one better leave &quot;quantum spiritu=\r\nality&quot; (Adwaita Vedanta) and focus on normal spirituality. However, when on=\r\ne&#39;s awareness becomes very subtle and one starts to deal with mystical expe=\r\nriences, deities etc, one must pay attention to Adwaita Vedanta. Otherwise,=\r\n one will commit errors!!\n\n \n\n10.  An excellent masterpiece of an example a=\r\nnd clarity!!!. I have no words to mention the beauty of this write-up. The =\r\npoint is, newton=E2=80=99s laws are applicable in a range, so it is rather =\r\na model than a law. The universe exists over a wide range from huge galaxie=\r\ns upto small atoms and molecules. Now under each range or orders of magnitu=\r\nde, certain simplifications/models/laws help us to fairly/accurately deal w=\r\nith =E2=80=9Cthe events in the range=E2=80=9D. So you may be successful in =\r\ndealing with the events in those restricted range of investigation/operatio=\r\nn/observation. But this may not necessarily lead you to the truth and moksh=\r\na. Because the range is still =E2=80=9Creal=E2=80=9D for you. So you contin=\r\nue to live in that =E2=80=9Crange=E2=80=9D  lifetime after lifetime.\n\n \n\nOn=\r\ne can live at quantum level, yet function at macro-level both simultaneousl=\r\ny, without mutual exclusion. And this is what Krishna deems as karma yoga o=\r\nr jeevan-mukta or Stitha-Pragnya. Such state of existence is the blessings =\r\nof the wise people. Company of wise people is like a nuclear-weapon to dest=\r\nroy the ignorance.\n\n \n\n \n\nThanks and Warm Regards,\n\nKannan.\n\n \n\n  _____  \n\n=\r\nFrom: Kannan Iyengar &lt;prof.kannan.iyengar@...&gt;\nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoo=\r\ngroups.com \nSent: Saturday, August 24, 2013 5:21 PM\nSubject: RE: [vedic-wis=\r\ndom] Re: which path to choose?-a dialog\n\n \n\n  \n\nDear Shri Narasimha Ji,\n\nNa=\r\nmasthe\n\n \n\n1.       I deeply appreciate and feel grateful for having shared=\r\n your understandings. I would kindly request you to permit me to share my u=\r\nnderstandings which stand in definite contrast with that of yours. I would =\r\nalso request your noble self to allow me to point out a number of flaws, wh=\r\nich I consider as a liberty bestowed on debating scholars. Of course, we do=\r\nn=E2=80=99t become great if we are =E2=80=9Cscholars=E2=80=9D because a sch=\r\nolar is essentially a person who continues to learn without a pause. I woul=\r\nd view this as an opportunity to rectify our understandings.\n\n \n\n2.       F=\r\nirst of all you quoted Swami Vivekananda as a stamping authority to support=\r\n/strengthen your argument. Let me tell you that truth/clarity does not need=\r\n any support, because it stands itself as a support for all.(In Hindi, =E2=\r\n=80=9Csatya ko pramaan ki aavashyakta nahi hai, satya swayam apna pramaan h=\r\nai=E2=80=9D)\n\n \n\n3.       Secondly, if what you have quoted from Swami Vive=\r\nkananda is true, then I am skeptical about Swami Vivekananda=E2=80=99s unde=\r\nrstandings himself. Let me tell you that divinity of soul is ever-existing =\r\nlike Sun (Sadaa Jaagati Jyoti)(ever shining light). So do you need any effo=\r\nrt to manifest it? Do you mean to say that the ever-shining Brahman is at t=\r\nhe mercy of our efforts to get itself manifested? Perhaps..But let us ponde=\r\nr what actually caused that sunlight to be eclipsed? Let me tell you that t=\r\nhe very idea of considering that divinity to be eclipsed is ignorance; and =\r\nconsequently trying to make an effort to remove that eclipse, is a greater =\r\nignorance. Any act done under ignorance will yield only further bondage and=\r\n eclipse, and trap the soul into the chakravyuha(tornado) of the maaya.\n\n \n=\r\n\n4.       The key idea here is that when we start with an assumption which =\r\nitself is faulty, then our whole calculation based on that assumption goes =\r\nfaulty. So there is no point in proceeding further beyond this, or else it =\r\n is just a waste of time, without true/clarity of vision dawning on us.\n\n \n=\r\n\n5.       I would humbly request your noble self to view it as a healthy sc=\r\nholarly debate, which necessitates being blunt and straightforward, without=\r\n being circumbulatory. This will be in the general interest and welfare of =\r\nall the earnest seekers.\n\n \n\n6.       I humbly request your noble self to p=\r\neruse my understandings, and bless us with further insights.\n\n \n\nThanks and=\r\n Warm Regards,\n\nKannan\n\n \n\nFrom: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com [mailto:vedic=\r\n-wisdom@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of Narasimha P.V.R. Rao\nSent: Saturday, =\r\nAugust 24, 2013 7:34 AM\nTo: sohamsa@yahoogroups.com; Vedic Wisdom\nSubject: =\r\n[vedic-wisdom] Re: which path to choose?-a dialog\n\n \n\n  \n\nNamaste friends,\n=\r\n \nI am cc&#39;ing this to vedic-wisdom yahoogroup because of the spiritual cont=\r\nent.\n \nI agree with Vishnu ji&#39;s comment on a specific point in Maja ji&#39;s ni=\r\nce write-up:\n \n&gt; &gt; *Also, one is supposed to choose only one ayana for one =\r\nlifetime and\n&gt; &gt; master it to as perfect as possible. *\n&gt; \n&gt;  I am not enti=\r\nrely sure if the above statement is correct. It is very much\n&gt; possible and=\r\n in fact is a measure of self realized people.\n \nIndeed, one can carve one&#39;=\r\ns own niche by combining multiple paths. They are not meant to be mutually =\r\nexclusive.\n \nI&#39;ll quote Swami Vivekananda from his book &quot;Raja Yoga&quot; where h=\r\ne makes a comment on the 4 paths:\n \n&quot;Each soul is potentially divine. The g=\r\noal is to manifest this divinity within by controlling nature: external and=\r\n internal. Do this either by work or worship or psychic control, or philoso=\r\nphy - by one, or more, or all of these - and be free.&quot;\n \nHere are my 2 cent=\r\ns.\n \nJnana yoga emphasizes on philosophization and wisdom. Karma yoga empha=\r\nsizes on work and detachment. Raja yoga emphasizes on self-control and self=\r\n-mastery. Bhakti yoga emphasizes on devotion and surrender to Supreme. One =\r\ncan pick whatever is natural to one and try to develop that quality. Howeve=\r\nr, wisdom, detached action, self-control and surrender to the Supreme are n=\r\not mutually exclusive. As one of these qualities develops nicely in one, ot=\r\nhers will automatically develop too! Finally, a realized person (i.e. one i=\r\nn &quot;Yoga&quot; or oneness) will have all these qualities fully blossomed.\n \nForge=\r\nt about horoscope, navamsa, vimsamsa, nakshatramsa etc. Irrespective of tha=\r\nt, I strongly recommend against Raja yoga for 99% of humanity. Even Ramakri=\r\nshna advised against it. Controlling body and mind and forcing the psychic =\r\nlife force to purify and ascend requires strict yama and niyama and clean n=\r\nadis. In this age of polluted air, water and food, nadis accumulate great a=\r\nmounts of obstructions and Raja yoga can be dangerous. This is not just my =\r\nview, but what Ramakrishna explicitly taught in &quot;Gospel of Ramakrishna&quot; (on=\r\ne of the greatest spiritual texts IMHO). He discouraged several of his sish=\r\nyas from pursuing Raja Yoga. He taught it to Vivekananda, but did not encou=\r\nrage even him to practice it.\n \nJnana yoga is brilliant, but there is a dis=\r\ntinct danger of falling into the delusional trap of pseudo-wisdom. People o=\r\nf this age are not sincere/honest/smart enough for it. It is easy to delude=\r\n that &quot;all is Brahman. I am Brahman. Whatever I do, it&#39;s ok - it doesn&#39;t ma=\r\ntter. It&#39;s all a delusion anyway&quot; without fully overcoming all innate condi=\r\ntioning that reinforces duality in consciousness every instant. Kind of lik=\r\ne declaring wisely in a movie that &quot;it&#39;s just a movie and not reality&quot;, but=\r\n flinching in every scary scene, crying in every sad scene etc. Without abs=\r\nolute honesty, sincerely and earnestness, jnana yoga can be problematic too=\r\n. A long path of constant contemplation and self-correction can be reduced =\r\nto a quick delusional jump to the end.\n \nIMHo, for most people in this age,=\r\n Bhakti yoga and Karma yoga are the most suitable and safest.\n \nBest regard=\r\ns,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology & Spirituality Resources: http://www.VedicA=\r\nstrologer.org &lt;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&gt;  \n--------\n \n--- In sohamsa=\r\n@yahoogroups.com, Vishnu Jandhyala &lt;jvishnu@...&gt; wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt; Dear Ms. Maja,\n=\r\n&gt; \n&gt; Namaste\n&gt; \n&gt; Now different type of 4 yogas based on ayana/kendra:\n&gt; &gt;\n=\r\n&gt; &gt; Dharma ayana - Gyana yoga- lagna and its trines\n&gt; &gt; Artha ayana - Karma=\r\n yoga - 10th bhava and its trines\n&gt; &gt; Kama ayana - Raja yoga- 7th bhava and=\r\n its trines\n&gt; &gt; Moksha ayana - Bhakti yoga - 4th bhava and its trines\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt;=\r\n &gt; These 4 yogas are listed in Bhagavat Gita, you can check it, I assure\n&gt; =\r\n&gt; there are four of them. Though it is very indicative you skipped Rajayoga=\r\n (\n&gt; &gt; controlling own senses) on your list...\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Anyway, for which ay=\r\nana will native decide is seen in Navamsha varga. Do\n&gt; &gt; you know how to se=\r\ne it?\n&gt; &gt; *Also, one is supposed to choose only one ayana for one lifetime =\r\nand\n&gt; &gt; master it to as perfect as possible. *\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; \n&gt;  I am not entirely =\r\nsure if the above statement is correct. It is very much\n&gt; possible and  in =\r\nfact is a measure of self realized people.\n&gt; \n&gt; *It is not possible for a h=\r\numan being to take two or more ayanas at the\n&gt; &gt; same time... well, one can=\r\n not go backwards and forward/left and right at\n&gt; &gt; the same time, can he/s=\r\nhe? :)*\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; Hmmm....well..............suppose a Guru were to suggest =\r\nto his/her pupil\n&gt; to stop a particular mantra and instead do some other ma=\r\nntra, isn&#39;t that\n&gt; change of direction? Aren&#39;t mantras the harbinger of Gat=\r\ni (direction)? BTW,\n&gt; in sadhana, one has to begin with Karma yoga, then Bh=\r\nakti, then Gnana and\n&gt; finally Raja yoga.\n&gt; \n&gt; Benefits of Karma yoga ---&gt;V=\r\ninaya (Humility),\n&gt; Benefits of Bhakti yoga ---&gt; Viveka (Intelligence),\n&gt; B=\r\nenefits of Gnana yoga ---&gt; Vignana (Liberating knowledge),\n&gt; Benefits of Ra=\r\nja yoga ----&gt; Vichakshana (Wisdom) & Vimukti (Emancipation)\n\n&gt; Without vina=\r\nya there is no viveka, without viveka there is no vignana,\n&gt; without vignan=\r\na there is no vichakshana, without vichakshana there is no\n&gt; vimukti! :-)\n&gt;=\r\n \n&gt; warm regards,\n&gt; Vishnu\n\ncid:image001.jpg@01CEA49B.B3CF0C60cid:image002.=\r\njpg@01CEA49B.B3CF0C60\n\n\r\n------=_NextPart_001_0008_01CEA4CB.C080DCB0\r\nContent-Type: text/html;\n\tcharset=&quot;utf-8&quot;\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;html xmlns:v=3D&quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml&quot; xmlns:o=3D&quot;urn:schemas-micr=\r\nosoft-com:office:office&quot; xmlns:w=3D&quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word&quot; =\r\nxmlns:m=3D&quot;http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2004/12/omml&quot; xmlns=3D&quot;http:=\r\n//www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40&quot;&gt;\n\n&lt;head&gt;\n&lt;meta http-equiv=3DContent-Type conten=\r\nt=3D&quot;text/html; charset=3Dutf-8&quot;&gt;\n&lt;meta name=3DGenerator content=3D&quot;Microso=\r\nft Word 12 (filtered medium)&quot;&gt;\n&lt;!--[if !mso]&gt;\n&lt;style&gt;\nv&#92;:* {behavior:url(#d=\r\nefault#VML);}\no&#92;:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\nw&#92;:* {behavior:url(#defaul=\r\nt#VML);}\n.shape {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\n&lt;/sty