parate, distinct, dua=\r\nl entities.\nWhen you are truly disposed off in non-duality, you cannot make=\r\n any such\nstatements.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=3DMsoNormal style=\r\n=3D&#39;margin-left:.5in&#39;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;font-size:10.0pt;\nfont-family:&quot;A=\r\nrial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:red&#39;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;font-size:=\r\n10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\ncolor:black&#39;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\nThough eve=\r\nrything is Self, Self is that which is unborn and un-perishing. We\nare surr=\r\nounded by many manifestations of Self that are transient, i.e. they are\nbor=\r\nn and they perish. When we come in contact with them, we do not focus on\nth=\r\neir imperishable essence, but focus on the transient/perishable portion tha=\r\nt\nis more readily perceptible to our senses, manas, buddhi and chitta.&lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\nThis perishable/transient portion is what we mean by covering/ec=\r\nlipse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span\nstyle=3D&#39;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-seri=\r\nf&quot;;color:#1F497D&#39;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=\r\n=3D&#39;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2&#39;&gt;&lt;![if !supportLists]&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;sp=\r\nan\nstyle=3D&#39;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:red&#39;&gt;&lt;=\r\nspan\nstyle=3D&#39;mso-list:Ignore&#39;&gt;6.&lt;span style=3D&#39;font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman=\r\n&quot;&#39;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;![endif]&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span sty=\r\nle=3D&#39;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\n&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:red&#39;&gt;No Dea=\r\nr Vipravara(learned person). This\nperishable transient portion is not eclip=\r\nse/covering/bondage. How can you have\na perishable entity, when the only en=\r\ntity that exist is itself imperishable.\nLet me take an example. Lets have a=\r\n gold metal. Lets make three entities with\nthat gold-viz.1. bangles 2. Neck=\r\nlace 3. Ear-rings. Each have different entities\nand functions and propertie=\r\ns and behavior and of course name. Now let us focus\non bangle. Bangle is so=\r\nmething which is=C2=A0 circular, and appears different from\nnecklace and ea=\r\nr-rings. Now, I take a 20 gm gold, and give it a shape and name\nand call it=\r\n bangle. Now, does the bangle exist in true sense? No. Now, I melt\nthe bang=\r\nle, it turns back to 20 gm gold with no shape and name. So what was\nexistin=\r\ng throughout is the =E2=80=9Cgold=E2=80=9D itself, and nothing else. Now yo=\r\nu call this\nbangle as a perishable entity. But the point is -it is not any =\r\nentity at all,\nin the first place. It is only a verbal and fictitious entit=\r\ny existing only in\nwords and mind, not in actuality. Gold is the only entit=\r\ny existing in\nactuality. Bangle is just a name given to a form and shape of=\r\n=C2=A0 gold.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=3DMsoListParagraph&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;spa=\r\nn style=3D&#39;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\ncolor:red&#39;&gt;&lt;=\r\no:p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=3DMsoListParagraph&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=\r\n=3D&#39;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\ncolor:red&#39;&gt;Now let =\r\nme come back to what eclipse/covering/bondage is. The point\nis there is no =\r\nsuch thing. It is only an illusion or imagination that we are\nbonded/eclips=\r\ned/covered. The very fact to consider gold to be eclipsed as\nbangle, and ba=\r\nngle to be perishable, transient entity, etc=E2=80=94all this is avidya.&lt;o:=\r\np&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=3DMsoListParagraph&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;font=\r\n-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\ncolor:red&#39;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/o:p=\r\n&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=3DMsoListParagraph&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;font-size:1=\r\n0.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\ncolor:red&#39;&gt;Let me give you an inci=\r\ndence of a beautiful Himalayan Sage called\nSwami Rama with his=C2=A0 Master=\r\n. Once Swami Rama asked his master to teach him what\navidya or maaya or ill=\r\nusion is? His master explained that avidya is individual\nillusion/ignorance=\r\n and maaya is cosmic illusion or ignorance. Swami Raama\nfurther asked the n=\r\nature of avidya. His master told that he will explain it\nlater. Then sudden=\r\nly his master jumped on a tree and held it tightly clinging\nonto its trunk =\r\nand hugging it with his legs crossed across the trunk of the\ntree. He shout=\r\ned=E2=80=9DRaamaa, Raamaa, please help me, save me.I am trapped by this\ntre=\r\ne. =E2=80=9C Swami Raamaa laughed and said =E2=80=9CHow silly? How can this=\r\n tree trap you?\nIt has no power to trap you. It is you who have caught hold=\r\n of it. Just make a\ndecision to quit that hold. Then you will be free=E2=80=\r\n=9D His master smiled. And said\nthis is what I mean by illusion or avidya. =\r\nThough it has got no power to\neclipse the Self, yet it appears to have ecli=\r\npsed the self. This illusion\noccurs when the intellect is rendered blind, a=\r\nnd not in the state of =E2=80=9Cpragnya=E2=80=9D.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;=\r\n\n\n&lt;p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D&#39;margin-left:.5in&#39;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;font-size:=\r\n10.0pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:black&#39;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\nSuppo=\r\nse one&#39;s leg is cut off, blood starts to gush out and one is about to die\ni=\r\nn a little time. Can one remain equanimous during that time and genui